=== Macedonian present tense ===

The present tense in Macedonian is expressed using imperfective verbs. The following table shows the conjugation of the verbs &quot;write&quot; (&quot;пишува/pišuva&quot;), &quot;speak&quot; (&quot;зборува/zboruva&quot;), &quot;want&quot; (&quot;сака/saka&quot;) and &quot;open&quot; (&quot;отвaра/otvara&quot;).

==Sinitic languages==
In Wu Chinese, unlike other Sinitic languages (Varieties of Chinese), some tenses can be marked, including the present tense. For instance, in Suzhounese and Old Shanghainese, the word is used. The particle is placed at the end of a clause, and when a tense is referenced, the word order switches to SOV.

In a sentence such as &quot;&quot;, it would be the perfective aspect in Standard Mandarin, whereas this would be analysed as the present tense in contemporary Shanghainese, where has undergone lenition to .

